# template-ignore — known intentional divergences from the template (keepers).
#
# Paths listed here are skipped by /push-openbrain-claude-starter and
# /pull-openbrain-claude-starter during drift inventory: they never surface as
# candidates, so recurring known drift costs zero review tokens. Both skills
# report a one-line count of ignored paths per run, so nothing is silently
# hidden.
#
# Format: one path or glob per line, relative to the vault root.
#   .claude/skills/daily-brief/SKILL.md      (exact file)
#   .obsidian/*                              (glob)
# Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored.
#
# Do NOT list upstream-PR candidates here (e.g. a hook script while its PR
# against the template is pending) — those must keep surfacing in inventory
# until merged. CLAUDE.md also stays out: both skills already handle it
# hunk-by-hunk, and a whole-file ignore would hide template-relevant edits.
#
# This file itself is the seed entry: each vault maintains its own keeper
# list, which is itself an intentional divergence from the template.

.openbrain/template-ignore
